column1: When will the US Congress agree to a new budget resolution?
column5: ['Before 9 August 2021', 'Between 9 August 2021 and 30 September 2021', 'Not before 1 October 2021']

column6: These idiots don't want anything passed to jam up the whole system and there aren'y enough who benefit to have the guts to stand up to Trump..
It is complicated but the pressure on both sides can accelerate.
Pressure by both sides to prove they can get SOMETHING done, will drive negotiations toward a resolution before Oct 1.

@Jprice94 @mkarbowsky @Pablo_Vargas The budget process is going to be very complicated. Even if Democrats want to reach an agreement on reconciliation, Manchin and Sinema are going to make this a painful process. But I think they will want to get something close to finished before the start of the next fiscal year.
Republicans have no reason to approve anything with Biden's name on it. Well Mr, Madison, how's that constitution thing working?
